gomodel:SYNGO_4904  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: \"Syndecan-2 is important for dendritic spine formation\". Knockdown with shRNA reduces formation of protrusions from dendrites (Fig. 1). Syndecan-2 positive protrusion opposed by structures contained the presynaptic marker synaptophysin (Fig. 10A). Syndecan-2 acts via neurofibromin-Ena/VASP signaling pathway on dendritic spinogenesis (Fig. 10). Experimental description: Hippocampal neuronal cultures were performed as described previously\n(Wang et al., 2004; Lin et al., 2006). In the former paper it is mentioned that \"Hippocampal neurons from embryonic day 18-20 rat brains were dissociated and cultured in Neurobasal medium,...\" PMID: 15066269" ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0001-9377-7414" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0269-0311" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-9880-1214" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-9681-3318" ;
        dc:date           "2023-01-29" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_BP_4904" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10116" .

